Need-to-haves:
1. As a visitor, I want to see a directory of the restaurants available.
2. As a visitor, when I click on a restaurant, I want to be able to see:
address
neighbourhood
price range
summary
phone number
menu
a list of available timeslots
3. As a visitor, I want to sign up for a customer account so that I can make reservations online
4. As a customer, I want to be able to make a reservation online
5. As a customer, I want to be able to set the number of people
6. As a customer, I want to be able to cancel a reservation
7. As a customer, I want to be able to see all my reservations
8. As the restaurant owner, I want to be able to list my reseervations
9. As the restaurant owner, I want to see the list of the weeks reservations

Nice-to-have:
1. Customer can filter categories (cuisine, neighbourhood, price) for viewing restaurants
2. Customer can upload a review of the restaurants
3. Customer can edit your reservation
4. Restaurant owner can edit restaurant
5. Restaurant owner can change the 1-hr capacity

To consider:
1. Photo uploads (for both customers and owners) of restaurant
2. Loyalty points

Initial need-to-have assumptions:
1. A restaurant can only hold 100 people in any given time slot.
2. A restaurant can only be open from 11am - 8pm, 7 days a week.
3. A reservation can be for a party of 2 to 20 people.
